<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/t5-amia2005_0106/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div></section></section><section id="sec13"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">4.3 Results of the extrinsic evaluation</h3>
<p>KB-χ<sup>2</sup> and KB-PCI had moderate sensitivities (0.615 and 0.435 respectively) and
high specificities (0.789 and 0.749 respectively). The paired <em>t</em> test demonstrated a significantly higher sensitivity of KB-χ<sup>2</sup> compared to that of KB-PCI (<em>p</em> value &lt; 0.01). There was no statistical difference between their specificities (<em>p</em> value = 0.29). (<a href="#t6-amia2005_0106" class="usa-link">Table 6</a>)</p>
